ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Is information about this pregnancy available?
Subject related information (e.g the affection, phenotype, disease information, etc.).

Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2, Daily
e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: Pregnancy Start date of last menses

Notes: 1=Not known at this date; 2=Still Birth; 3=Uneventful (normal/healthy baby); 4=Neonatal death; 5=Induced Abortion; 6=Spontaneous Abortion; 7=Birth defects

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Study; The code for each individual study
Notes: e.g., the name of the study in multi-grant collections
0=Negative; 1=Positive; 2=Test not conducted; -7=Refused; 9=NA;3=Not pregnant (per pregnancy test); 4=Not pregnant (has not reached menarche); 5=Pregnancy suspected, but not confirmed; 6 = Equivocal

ElementDescription: Current Birth Control or Reproductive Status
Notes: 1=Oral; 2=Hormonal Injections; 3=Hormonal Implants; 4=Contraceptive Patches; 5=Ring; 6=Intrauterine device, hormonal; 7=Intrauterine device, non-hormonal; 8=Barrier method; 9=Spermicide; 10 Post-menopausal for > 1 year; 11=Bilateral tubal ligation, bilateral oophorectomy, or hysterectomy; 12=Abstinence; 99 = other

-1.5 = Pre-Screening; -1 = Screening; 0 = Baseline; ## = Visit ## (from 1 to 10); Whole numbers = standard monthly visits; #.001 - #.009 = Unscheduled; #.1 = End of Phase 1; #.2 = End of Phase 2; #.3 = End of Phase 3; #.4 = End of Open Choice Phase; #.5 = End of Study; #.6 = Genetic Analysis; 1000=all visits

ElementDescription: If N/A checked (pregnancy test), please select one reason

Notes: 1= Yes ; 2= No ; -99= NA; 77= Refused ; 88= Missing; 3=not assessed

ElementDescription: Staff code number of person completing this form
If equivocal, what was the retest result
